<$TOP/mkfiles/mkfile.proto

# See mkfiles/arm64/mkfile for the flag rationale (-fsigned-char, gnu89, ...).
CC=gcc -c --std=gnu89 -Wno-cpp -fsigned-char
LD=gcc
AS=gcc
O=o

# used in tests/: the RISC-V (rv64) lineage. ja/jl are the *same* binaries
# as ia/il (assemblers/ia/mkfile, linkers/il/mkfile install them under both
# names); their main()s auto-select thechar='j' (64-bit) from argv[0]'s
# basename or a -j flag, the original inferno 'i'/'j' dual-width riscv
# convention -- there is no separate top-level arch letter for riscv64
# the way arm64 got its own '7' distinct from arm's '5'. Object ext .j.
#
# CC_ is NOT wired to a working jc yet: ic's thechar='j' selection is
# entirely commented out (see compilers/ic/mkfile and compilers/ic/txt.c's
# "TODO: trick for ic and jc"), so there is no C-level riscv64 compiler
# yet -- only ja/jl (assembler/linker), enough for tests/s/* (hand-written
# assembly) but not tests/c/* until ic's dual-mode is restored.
O_=j
CC_=ic	# TODO: not really riscv64, see above -- ic can't emit thechar='j' yet
LD_=jl
AS_=ja
AR_=iar
